helpdesk-ticket.subject: Jenzabar enchancement
helpdesk-ticket.description: Beth/Jen--we had on our Ann list a project that you may be able to assist us with. We are hoping to have some place in Jenzabar where all on one screen we can record all of the random things we track for students for reporting purposes. As people are requesting more information, we are finding that we need to track more and more things. It will be easier to query information if it is all in one table. What I envision is one user-defined screen with a whole bunch of user fields that we can use as needed and add data to when needed. We don't really want these things in hidden tables that things are scripted into...we want to be able to see and enter data on a screen. I am just putting in a ticket to record it for a future discussion at some point after the upgrade and before Ann's next visit.

Hello Mohammed, I checked in Blackboard to see if these two instructors use this tool. However, neither instructor posted their syllabus to Blackboard. However, the Math Department has a policy that all of their instructors must follow the Academic Catalog with all of the course outcomes in order to teach at MSOE. I’ve attached those two documents, as this may be what they use as their syllabus.
They must also follow the school’s academic policies, which are provided on our webpage at: http://catalog.msoe.edu/content.php?catoid=10&navoid=285&hl=%22grading%22&returnto=search This includes the grading scale, information about GPAs and academic standing, which I think will also meet your needs.
Pat Hurlbut, Director of Instructional Design

Any help you might be able to provide? I already tried running the command \\printers.msoe.edu in terminal to no success. Thanks
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
I received a word document of how to connect to the printing system on windows but it didn't include any instructions about doing so on Mac OSX.
Any help you might be able to provide?
I already tried running the command \\printers.msoe.edu in terminal to no success.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Nathan,
On the desktop of your computer, press Command and K at the same time. After doing this, type in smb://printers.msoe.edu. You should then get a prompt for entering your username and password. For username, put in MSOE\username and your password as your msoe password. Next, double click on Follow you Printing and the printers should be added.
If you have any more issues please respond to this ticket or call the helpdesk at (414)-277-7288. Ticket: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/344 Thanks, Kevin

helpdesk-ticket.subject: printer problems in CC202 (CBM)
helpdesk-ticket.description:
We have an HP Color Laserjet M553 PCL6 in the CBM. The printer was moved over the summer in hopes that it would print faster using a different Ethernet line. Since it was moved, I have been unable to print to this printer, and in the past week, MOST of the office computers have lost the ability to print to this printer. (Only 1 computer can print to this printer, and the time to send to the printer is incredibly long - a test print page took 2-3 minutes.)
The port number for the printer on one computer is 10.146.26.30 (it doesn't work). On the computer that works, the port # is 9100. Neither of these IP addresses is what we entered when we installed the printers.
We need to get this printer working; the backup printer we are using is much more costly to run.
Someone is typically in the office from 7:30 am until 4:30 pm.
Thanks.
Margaret

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Margaret,
Could you please try re-adding the printer? First, get the correct IP address off of the printer which should be available on the screen on the printer. Then follow these instructions to add the printer to windows:
1. Click Start and select Drivers and Printers. 2. Click Add Printer. 3. Select Add a network, wireless, or Bluetooth printer then click Next. 4. Select The printer I want isn't listed then click Next. 5. Select Add a printer using a TCP/IP address or hostname then click Next. 6. In the Hostname or IP address box type in the IP Address of the printer then click Next. 7. Select the type of printer you are using then click Next. 8. Type in a printer name an select Set as the default printer if you would like this as your default then click Next. 9. Your printer has now been added, you can Print a test page to test that it is working correctly.
Ticket: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/363 Thanks, Kevin
helpdesk-note.body-html:

3. Select Add a network, wireless, or Bluetooth printer then click Next.
4. Select The printer I want isn't listed then click Next.
5. Select Add a printer using a TCP/IP address or hostname then click Next.
6. In the Hostname or IP address box type in the IP Address of the printer then click Next.

8. Type in a printer name an select Set as the default printer if you would like this as your default then click Next.
9. Your printer has now been added, you can Print a test page to test that it is working correctly.

I tried this morning to get into the MICROS system per our training yesterday. I was able to connect to the remote desktop with no issue (by using the IP 155.92.194.13, and not the host-mask, as the host-mask seems to be setup improperly). After getting into the system I tried to start the "EMC" software as directed... but was IMMEDIATELY stuck. Nobody besides Sheila has been given admin privileges on that machine, and therefore it is IMPOSSIBLE to run the program "as administrator" (as was directed in the instructions). helpdesk-note.body:
Hi calderonea, Ticket: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/420 This is a perfectly normal behavior for the paystub website. It will only generate a valid PDF ion dates that have checks. If any other day is selected then it will generate a blank white PDF. If it is not generating paystubs on dates when you got paid, I would suggest using internet explorer as your browser. Reply to this ticket if you are still having issues.
Thanks MSOE Information Technology Cameron Wilson

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Naomi, Ticket: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/422
I have a guide that you can use. Follow this exactly and let me know if you have any questions at any point in the installation, I would be more than happy to assist.
**Also please note that you must be connected to the MSOE Internal domain wireless or plugged into an Ethernet port on campus in order for the install to work. If you plan to VPN in using global protect and install the product let me know and I can give you another guide for that as well.**
Best Regards, Sam West MSOE IT - Assistant Systems Administrator

helpdesk-ticket.subject: laptops
helpdesk-ticket.description: i just got my laptop and when trying to download Spotify, I kept coming across issues installing it. Is Spotify blocked from the school computers?
helpdesk-ticket.description-html: i just got my laptop and when trying to download Spotify, I kept coming across issues installing it. Is Spotify blocked from the school computers?

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Mitchell, Ticket: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/439
Group Policy blocks any program from self extracting and executing at the same time, this is protective measure put in place to protect users from getting harmful viruses. The only problem is when downloading some programs it will throw an error because that specific program both extracts and executes at the same time. There is a little trick to installing these programs manually though. I will attach a guide in my next email to you, hang tight.
Best Regards, Sam West MSOE IT - Assistant Systems Administrator
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Mitchell,

Ticket: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/439

Group Policy blocks any program from self extracting and executing at the same time, this is protective measure put in place to protect users from getting harmful viruses. The only problem is when downloading some programs it will throw an error because that specific program both extracts and executes at the same time. There is a little trick to installing these programs manually though. I will attach a guide in my next email to you, hang tight.


Best Regards, 
Sam West
MSOE IT - Assistant Systems Administrator

Hi Jacob Voller, Ticket: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/455
I would also like to add that you can set up security questions and change your password whenever at https://pwdreg.msoe.edu/default.aspx Moreover if you just want to quickly change your password you could also take these steps. Change your Windows password
Press Ctrl+Alt+Delete, and then click Change a password. Type your old password, type your new password, type your new password again to confirm it, and then press Enter. The next time you connect to the campus network your new windows password will change all of your single sign on passwords to match it.
-Sam

Hi mickschlcj, Ticket: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/458 If you still having issues with it automaticly sending you to the password reset page, then i would recommend clearing the catch in chrome. Here are the steps in doing so.
In the top-right corner of Chrome, click the Chrome menu . Select More tools > Clear browsing data. In the dialog that appears, select the checkboxes for the types of information that you want to remove. Use the menu at the top to select the amount of data that you want to delete. Select beginning of time to delete everything. Click Clear browsing data
Reply to this ticket if you still have issues

  3. In the dialog that appears, select the checkboxes for the types of information that you want to remove.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Tyler Braun, Ticket: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/467 Its possible that the wirelsss card is simply disabled. There are two buttons above the keyboard on the left hand side of the laptop. The right one controls the wifi radio. If this light is red simply hit the button and it should turn blue and you should have wifi service again. If this is not the case i would recommend bringing the machine into the CCIT helpdesk and we can repair it for you. Reply to this ticket if you have any questions.
Thanks, MSOE Information Technology Cameron Wilson 414-277-7288 helpdesk@msoe.edu

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Projector turned off and required restart 20 minutes into a meeting
helpdesk-ticket.description: This morning, faculty of the SE program were having a program meeting in L304. Chris Taylor was projecting to both projectors using HDMI connection. The image was fine for approximately 20-30 minutes. At about 20-30 minutes into the meeting, the image that was projected went away and both projectors said "No HDMI Signal". I went to the touch screen panel and attempted to adjust to other sources, but none of them would go live. The light was green on the touch screen indicating it was still receiving a signal from the device and the laptop still indicated it was connected. After the system was shutdown and restarted, it immediately came up with the HDMI display on screen. My concern is this happened after 20-30 minutes, right in the middle of a typical lecture.

helpdesk-ticket.description:
IT Staff:
I just discovered that installing and running the version of EEC available for installation from the network results in an expired license message. Please look into this. It is my understanding that we bought a perpetual license for this software a few years ago (maybe more recently). It is used by the BE and ME programs. The e-mail exchanges below provides some context regarding the situation.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: FW: New printers in the library
helpdesk-ticket.description:
FYI -
Please respond to Sarah.
Thanks Steve
From: Rowell, Sarah Sent: Friday, September 04, 2015 12:55 PM To: diFilipo, Stephen <difilipo@msoe.edu> Subject: FW: New printers in the library
Hi IT,
We have some questions about the two new printers that we hope you'll be able to answer. Once the students are back, we'll need to be well-versed in the capabilities of these machines so we can in-turn answer patron questions.
1. Can we copy in color? We used to be able to do this on our small staff copier and the old printer/copier/scanner, but both have been removed. Does the new public printer allow for color copying? If not, can we at least scan in color and then send it to print in color as a possible work around?
2. How do we know if/how much we are being charged on the color printer? There is no readout to let us know how much any transaction costs or how much remains on the card.
3. The color printer can print black and white, but if you print from it are you automatically charged as if it were in color? Do we have to make sure the color printer is labeled for color printing only so students don't get upset about being charged? If people are charged in error, what steps can they take for a refund?
4. What toner is required and who will be furnishing it? How do we order more?
5. If/when they break, who do we contact to fix them?

helpdesk-note.body: It might be the VPN client that was causing my account to be locked. After disconnecting that my account seems to have stopped locking. But I cannot use ssh to faculty-web when I don't have a VPN connection, so I'm still stuck.
helpdesk-note.body-html: It might be the VPN client that was causing my account to be locked.  After disconnecting that my account seems to have stopped locking.  But I cannot use ssh to faculty-web when I don't have a VPN connection, so I'm still stuck.

helpdesk-note.body: Still able to use email and my.msoe.edu now that VPN is disconnected, so I'm pretty sure the problem is there. I was going to try to download the latest client manually (mine kept saying there is an update, but it seemed to always quit the update process) so I went to https://sslvpn.msoe.edu/. When I put kruegerm and password there it does not accept it. So maybe something is wrong with my account as far as VPN settings? FWIW: I'm running Windows 7, my own laptop (not MSOE supplied).

FWIW: I'm running Windows 7, my own laptop (not MSOE supplied).

helpdesk-note.body: Please ignore the part about https://sslvpn.msoe.edu/, I just did not wait log enough for it to log in. I am trying the newer client now, I was able to download it after all.
helpdesk-note.body-html: Please ignore the part about  https://sslvpn.msoe.edu/, I just did not wait log enough for it to log in.  I am trying the newer client now, I was able to download it after all.

helpdesk-note.body: OK, after manually installing the VPN client it is all up to date. It does connect, but as before as soon as I connect my account locks and I have to do a password reset. So if VPN is disconnected I can connect to mail, my.msoe.edu, etc. If VPN is connected, account keeps locking up. Same password used in all cases.
helpdesk-note.body-html: OK, after manually installing the VPN client it is all up to date.  It does connect, but as before as soon as I connect my account locks and I have to do a password reset.  So if VPN is disconnected I can connect to mail, my.msoe.edu, etc.  If VPN is connected, account keeps locking up.  Same password used in all cases.

helpdesk-note.body: Figured out the lock out issue, I had MSOE printer connections but Windows still had an old password cached, so whenever I connected via VPN it tried to talk to the printers and the result was account lock out. So I seem to be able to connect to VPN now without locking my account. However, I still cannot ssh into faculty-web, it just keeps prompting for a password as though the password was bad. I'm using my global MSOE username (kruegerm) and password.
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Figured out the lock out issue, I had MSOE printer connections but Windows still had an old password cached, so whenever I connected via VPN it tried to talk to the printers and the result was account lock out.  So I seem to be able to connect to VPN now without locking my account.

However, I still cannot ssh into faculty-web, it just keeps prompting for a password as though the password was bad.  I'm using my global MSOE username (kruegerm) and password.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Can't reach mail server
helpdesk-ticket.description: I'm pretty sure it has to do with the password reset on 9/1, since that was the last time Outlook was able to reach the mail server. I did already reset my password, but I can't figure out how to edit it in Outlook.
helpdesk-ticket.description-html: I'm pretty sure it has to do with the password reset on 9/1, since that was the last time Outlook was able to reach the mail server. I did already reset my password, but I can't figure out how to edit it in Outlook.

helpdesk-note.body:
Dear Mr. Christopher Murphy-Veigelt, This email is in response to your following ticket regarding the outlook issue you are facing.
Ticket: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/569
As you expected, the outlook password needs to be changed. One way to do it is to delete the outlook password that the windows previously saved on your laptop. Once it is deleted, when you reopen the outlook, it should ask for password where in you enter the current password.
Follow the steps below in order to deleted the stored old outlook password.
Click the Start button and type-in "Credential Manager". A dialogue box should appear. In the dialogue box, under "Generic Credentials", click the vault that contains the outlook credentials. Click Remove from vault. Hit 'yes' when it asks for the confirmation to delete those credentials. Reopen Outlook. Now you should get a pop-up window asking you enter your credentials.
Once you enter your current password, your Outlook should get connected to Microsoft Exchange and your inbox should get updated with recent emails.
If this doesn't solve your issue, please reply to this email. I would be happy to assist you in solving the issue.
Please do not hesitate to contact IT help desk if you have any additional questions.
Vishwajith Reddy Variyala IT Support Technician 414-277-7288
For the first class I wish you lots of success and lots of new friends.
Good Luck On Your 1st Day At MSOE
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Dear Mr. Christopher Murphy-Veigelt,

This email is in response to your following ticket regarding the outlook issue you are facing.

Ticket: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/569

As you expected, the outlook password needs to be changed. One way to do it is to delete the outlook password that the windows previously saved on your laptop. Once it is deleted, when you reopen the outlook, it should ask for password where in you enter the current password. 

Follow the steps below in order to deleted the stored old outlook password. 
  1. Click the Start button  and type-in "Credential Manager". A dialogue box should appear.
  2. In the dialogue box, under "Generic Credentials", click the vault that contains the outlook credentials.
  3. Click Remove from vault.
  4. Hit 'yes' when it asks for the confirmation to delete those credentials.
  5. Reopen Outlook. Now you should get a pop-up window asking you enter your credentials.
Once you enter your current password, your Outlook should get connected to Microsoft Exchange and your inbox should get updated with recent emails.

If this doesn't solve your issue, please reply to this email. I would be happy to assist you in solving the issue.

Please do not hesitate to contact IT help desk if you have any additional questions.
 
Vishwajith Reddy Variyala
IT Support Technician
414-277-7288

For the first class I wish you lots of success and lots of new friends.
Good Luck On Your 1st Day At MSOE

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Department print queues unavailable
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hello,
This morning I noticed that department printers including L328, L350, and S353A are no longer receiving jobs sent to the print queues configured via morpheus and that Windows indicates the queues are offline, while morpheus itself still appears on the network.
I thought this might be related to the 8/13 announcement that Follow You Printing was moving from morpheus to printers. So, I attempted to install the print queues for the department printers from printers using the standard procedure (http://www.msoe.edu/docs/DOC-1928), but found only 8 department queues, none of which are linked to any of the printers in the Library or Science Buildings.
I appreciate your assistance regaining printer access as I so that I can print materials for my Tuesday morning classes.
Thank You,
Prof Durant, EECS, x7439

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Dr. Yoder,
The Helpdesk has asked me to verify that we can mark this ticket closed, so I wanted to make sure you understand how the relationship works between websites.
The following sites all participate in our Single Sign-On process: Outlook MS Office BOX HUB RAVE BlackBoard (when applicable) HandShake WebProd (Admissions Web)
If you sign into any one of these then visit another one of the sites, the SSO tool we use will open a tokenized authenticated session with that site as well. So if you were logged into MSOE.edu and browsed to getrave.com, SSO will sign you into RAVE automatically. You will not see this authentication, as SSO is designed to happen behind the scenes. It may appear that you have stayed logged into RAVE since your last visit. The tokenized browser session only lasts 8 hours, or until the browser is closed.
In your example of a user signed into a public computer (hopefully this scenario is rare, as we provide all faculty, all staff, and all full time students with laptops), the user would be automatically signed out after 8 hours, or when the browser was closed. Ultimately, though, each user is responsible for the security of their own account, particularly on a public device.
This should explain why getrave.com might appear to be logged in even if you hadn't used it recently.
Thanks,
